JOHANNESBURG, November 16 (ANA) – South African private equity firm, Pallinghurst Resources, on Thursday announced that its executive director, Priyank Thapliyal, was taking up the role of chief executive of Jupiter Mines. Pallinghurst holds an 18.4 percent stake in Jupiter Mines, an independent mining company based in Perth, Western Australia. It has a portfolio of projects in the Yilgarn region of Western Australia and the Kalahari Manganese Fields in the Northern Cape of South Africa. Thapliyal has resigned from his position at Pallinghurst with immediate effect. His responsibilities will be absorbed by the other executive directors. The board thanked Thapliyal for his past contributions, and said it looks forward to continue working with him as he further develops one of Pallinghurst’s important investments. African News Agency